text: The Colonel James Drane House is a historic house in French Camp, Mississippi, U.S.. It was built from 1846 to 1848 for James Drane, a state politician. It has been listed on the National Register of Historic Places since July 21, 1983. ==References== Category:Houses on the National Register of Historic Places in Mississippi Category:Houses completed in 1848 Category:Buildings and structures in Choctaw County, Mississippi
title: Colonel James Drane House
